725551f-a.text:
63rd Road, south side, Just east of 99th Street, showing the old J. Tompkins farmhouse. Tompkins was the owner in 1852; A. Backus in 18o0-73; and M. E. Lever in 1891. 63rd Road is the old North Hempstead Plank Road that led from Newtown to Flushing.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  April, 19P3

725552f-a.text:
63rd Road,(left not shown) south side, about 120 feet, east of 99th Street, showing the J. Tompkins house of 1852.
January 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

725553f-b.text:
63rd Road (formerly North Hempstead Plank Road) south side, at about 120 feet east of 99th Street. The house formerly stood on the south side of North Hempstead Plank Road west of 102nd Street. This set of 4 views shows the J. Tompkins farmhouse formerly known as 64 Old Mill Road. J. Tompkins, 1852; A Backus, 1850-1873; M. S. Lever, 1891; Dr. Lever, 1896; and Mrs. Lever in 1909 were owners of this property. The house was demolished in May 1926. Some of the outbuildings were still standing on the north side of 63rd Drive about 120 feet east of 99th Street in 1927. This set shows different angles of the house now going to ruin.
March 1925
Views 1, 2, 3 and 4
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
